  "event_preview": "Fuji Speedway is a 4.563 km (2.836 mi) road course at the foothills of Mount Fuji in Oyama, Shizuoka Prefecture — Toyota's home circuit and the fastest track on the Super GT calendar, built around a 1.5 km front straight that feeds a heavy braking zone at Turn 1. The Fuji GT 3 Hours Race GW Special is one of only two three-hour races on the 2026 calendar and the 31st edition of the Golden Week race dating back to 1994. With Sepang postponed to 2027, it is also the last race before a three-month break.\n\nThe GT500 qualifying record belongs to Kenta Yamashita, who set a 1:25.764 in the No. 14 ENEOS GR Supra during Q2 at the November 2021 round. The GT300 record is Hideki Yamauchi's 1:34.395 in the No. 61 Subaru BRZ from the same session.",
